<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RECONDITIONING ROTORS - INSPECTION - CRACKED ROTORS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CRACKED ROTORS</title>
        <para>Braking surface cracks are seen as radial cracks around the edge of the rotor at the outside or inside
            diameter of the braking surfaces (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401815">Figure 15
                <xref refid="f0401815"/>
            </hotlnk>
            ).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0401815" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0401815" filename="../figg04/G0401815.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. Cracked Rotor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Cracked rotors observed during shop inspection must be replaced, because as the cracks accelerate, they
            will eventually progress into the barrel section of the rotor and cause separation of the braking section
            from the mounting flange.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
